<TITLE> Court approves interrogation of Obaidul Kader at prison gate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 31 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Wednesday allowed investigators to question former state minister and AL leader Obaidul Kader at the prison gate in three corruption cases involving Tk 1.42 crore extorted from different contractors. Investigating officer and ACC assistant director Md Talebur Rahman appealed to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka to show the AL leader arrested in the three cases and to quiz him. Metropolitan magistrate Md Mizanur Rahman permitted the investigator to question Obaidul at the prison gate. On Sep 30, ACC assistant director Ashraful Islam filed the cases with Paltan police. According to case details, Obaidul took Tk 1.42 crore in bribes from different firms in exchange for awarding contracts and assuring bill payments. bdnews
